Package: clerkR
Title: Publication-Ready Tables for Biomedical Research
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Lucas G. S.", "Franca",
           email = "lucas.franca@northumbria.ac.uk",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-0853-1319"))
  )
Description: Transforms standard R data frames into publication-ready tables
    across a handful of common archetypes found in biomedical and neuroscience
    manuscripts: descriptive/Table 1 with group comparisons, heritability and
    variance components, correlation and partial correlation, regression
    coefficients, and simple descriptive summaries. Provides a unified
    rendering pipeline targeting 'gt' (Word/PDF), 'reactable' (HTML), and
    LaTeX outputs, with consistent theming, domain/section grouping, footnote
    handling for transformed variables, and FDR annotation.
